Data Visualization (incarceration)

Introduction

To know the population of each races in jail at Autauga County since 1970 to 2018, and the proportion of different races between 1990 to 2018. I created variables to compute proportion of different races. I uses the sum of totoal people from 15 to 64 years old in jail every years, and sum of total population from 15 to 64 years old of different races. Than I divided those two data, I got the proportion of differentraces in jail.

Racial population Proportion
Asian American / Pacific Islander Population Count: 0.93%
Black Population Count: 18.15%
Latinx Population Count: 1.82%
Native American Population Count: 0.42%
White Population Count: 78.68%

Trends over time charts

So in chart one, I use a line plot to show how does population changes annually between different races, and I use different colors to represent different races. In the chart, the blue line shows the population from 15 to 64 in jail, white line represent white people, black line represents black people, yellow line represents Asian and pacific islander, brown represent latinx, gray represent native Americans. Why I chose line plot to show the data is because, through the chart we can see clrealy, since 1990, the population of every race are increases, Whites are the largest racial group in prison.

Comparison

In chart two, I also use a line plot to show the comparison of populasion in jail between Asian& Pacific Islander American and native Americans. Because I found that in chart one, the population between these two races are close. So I do the chart two to compare this. Yellow represent Asian and Islander Americans, gray represent Native Americans. Through the graph we know that the Asian and Islander Americans keep increase, and the Native Americans increase in 1990 to 2000 and after 2000 it is relatively stable. The data is change around 150 every year. ### Mapping
